abstract: It’s the end of a tumultuous week for Wall Street, Washington and anyone with money in the stock markets or a retirement account, a five-day span of record climbs and precipitous drops. As President Bush tries once again to reassure investors, The Lede will once again track the day’s developments as markets and governments around the world grapple with the ongoing financial crisis. More business and financial coverage is available throughout nytimes.com.
